1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:04,170
Let me walk through a single day on the hybrid trial-ops platform.

2
00:00:04,470 --> 00:00:15,321
Five automations fire across the day — recurrent QC, SOP knowledge, eTMF filing, a timeline cascade, and risk-based monitoring.

3
00:00:15,621 --> 00:00:22,427
Every one follows the same shape: a trigger, an AI-drafted proposal, and a human who approves.

4
00:00:22,727 --> 00:00:26,630
Nothing reaches a validated system of record without that approval.

5
00:00:27,630 --> 00:00:31,991
That is the rule across all seventy-five automations on the platform.

6
00:00:32,291 --> 00:00:42,133
The agent drafts a proposal into a human-approval queue; nothing is filed, sent, or changed in a validated system until a human approves it.

7
00:00:42,433 --> 00:00:51,038
And the same sensitivity routing applies — participant-level data stays on the local model; non-sensitive work goes to cloud.

8
00:00:52,038 --> 00:00:52,853
Eight a.m.

9
00:00:53,153 --> 00:01:02,695
The nightly QC run catches a data discrepancy — an adverse-event onset date that falls after its resolution date, for one participant.

10
00:01:02,995 --> 00:01:14,374
Because it is participant-level data, the agent drafts the data query on the local model, zero egress — a clear, specific query citing the fields and the rule.

11
00:01:14,674 --> 00:01:20,269
The data manager reviews it, edits if needed, and issues it in the validated EDC.

12
00:01:20,569 --> 00:01:23,607
The agent never writes to the EDC itself.

13
00:01:24,607 --> 00:01:25,508
Ten-thirty.

14
00:01:25,808 --> 00:01:30,524
A CRA asks: what is our process for a missed PK sample?

15
00:01:30,824 --> 00:01:36,335
The assistant is grounded on the SOP library — non-sensitive, so cloud.

16
00:01:36,635 --> 00:01:40,956
It answers in plain language and cites the exact SOP and version.

17
00:01:41,256 --> 00:01:50,102
The CRA checks the cited SOP before acting; the controlled document stays the source of truth, not the model's paraphrase.

18
00:01:51,102 --> 00:01:52,020
One p.m.

19
00:01:52,320 --> 00:01:55,480
A monitoring visit report lands in the shared drive.

20
00:01:55,780 --> 00:02:05,947
The agent classifies it against the TMF reference model, proposes the filing location, and pre-fills the metadata — on the non-sensitive document.

21
00:02:06,247 --> 00:02:13,923
Nothing is filed yet: the TMF specialist confirms the classification and files it in the validated eTMF.

22
00:02:14,223 --> 00:02:17,029
The proposal is a draft in the approval queue.

23
00:02:18,029 --> 00:02:19,058
Three p.m.

24
00:02:19,358 --> 00:02:26,965
A confirmed change — the data cut moves from the seventeenth to the nineteenth — means downstream dates must shift.

25
00:02:27,265 --> 00:02:38,012
The agent computes the dependent cascade: soft-lock, dry-run TLFs, the DSMB pack, and drafts the Smartsheet update and a notification.

26
00:02:38,312 --> 00:02:42,316
The project manager reviews, adjusts, and applies it.

27
00:02:42,616 --> 00:02:44,470
The PM owns the timeline.

28
00:02:45,470 --> 00:02:46,418
Four-thirty.

29
00:02:46,718 --> 00:02:53,570
A risk-based-monitoring KRI crosses its quality tolerance limit — a site's query rate is too high.

30
00:02:53,870 --> 00:03:00,159
The agent packages the breach with its trend and the contributing records, and drafts the action note.

31
00:03:00,459 --> 00:03:08,295
The PM, or the central monitor, reviews the packaged signal and decides the response — perhaps a targeted visit.

32
00:03:08,595 --> 00:03:11,659
The system flags; the human decides.

33
00:03:12,659 --> 00:03:20,297
So across the day, the platform did the drafting; the humans approved; the validated systems owned the records.

34
00:03:20,597 --> 00:03:24,743
One shape every time — trigger, draft, approval.

35
00:03:25,043 --> 00:03:36,989
Sensitivity routed the engine, and the validated systems stayed authoritative: the EDC issued the query, the eTMF filed the document, Smartsheet held the timeline.

36
00:03:37,289 --> 00:03:41,804
The busywork is automated; judgment and accountability stay human.
